In this context, 1,3-Benzothiazole and toluene are both mentioned as components of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) detected in air samples from a facility. While they are categorized together as air contaminants and industrial solvents, there is no direct discussion of their interaction or specific relationship beyond their presence in the same analytical study. The mention of both compounds highlights their relevance as environmental pollutants but does not establish a significant connection between them.

Chemosphere 2010 Jun;80(3):279-85.

In this context, 1,3-Benzothiazole and Carbon Black are both components of crumb rubber material (CRM) derived from recycled tires. Carbon Black serves as a reinforcing agent in the rubber composition, while 1,3-Benzothiazole is mentioned as a vulcanization additive. Their relationship is primarily as constituents of the same material, contributing to the properties of CRM used in artificial turf installations. However, there is no detailed discussion of their interactions or specific roles beyond their inclusion in the rubber formulation.
